What if the software controlling one of the elevators suddenly crashes?

Has to have a method of detecting crash and method to reboot.


What if it doesn't crash, but hangs?

Timer of some sort, no reply? Reboot.


What if a message between machines is lost?

Should not happen, but resend message. 


What if the network cable is suddenly disconnected? Then re-connected?

Orders and current state should not be lost. Saved to another PC.


What if a user of the system is being a troll?

System should be robust enough to handle it.


What if the elevator car never arrives at its destination?

Reboot the system?
